The ANC MP was killed in the car accident near Paarl on Wednesday morning. JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma has sent condolences to the family of African National Congress (ANC) Member of Parliament (MP) Timothy Khoza who died when MPs were involved in a vehicle collision in Paarl.The vehicle carrying the MPs collided with a taxi on Wednesday morning.It s understood Khoza was killed on impact, while his injured colleagues from Parliament s Basic Education Committee were rushed to a hospital.The three injured MPs have been identified as Nomalungela Gina of the ANC, the Democratic Alliance's Ian Ollis and Cynthia Majeke of the United Democratic Movement.They ve been admitted to the Paarl Mediclinic.The contingent from the Basic Education Portfolio Committee was on their way to conduct oversight visits at schools in the area when the car they were travelling in overturned.The cause of the accident is not clear at this stage.Additional reporting by Lindsay Dentlinger.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)